'''Ronald G. Amundson''' is an American [[Environmental science|environmental scientist]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://dl.sciencesocieties.org/publications/authors/directory/profile/1223336 |title=Ronald G. Amundson |publisher=Science Societies |accessdate=December 27, 2017}}</ref> who is currently Professor at [[University of California, Berkeley]].<ref name=UCBerkely>{{Cite web |url=https://ourenvironment.berkeley.edu/people/ronald-amundson |title=Ronald G. Amundson |work=Our environment: People |publisher=University of California, Berkely |accessdate=December 27, 2017}}</ref>

==Research==
His interests are isotope [[biogeochemistry]], environment history & ethics, ecosystems, pedology and soils.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://vcresearch.berkeley.edu/faculty/ronald-g-amundson |title=Ronald G. Amundson |work=Vice=Chancellor Research |publisher=University of California, Berkely |accessdate=December 27, 2017}}</ref> His highest cited paper is "Rapid exchange between soil carbon and atmospheric carbon dioxide driven by temperature change"<ref>{{cite journal |author1=Trumbore, Susan E. |author2=Chadwick, Oliver A. |author3=Amundson, Ronald |title=Rapid Exchange between Soil Carbon and Atmospheric Carbon Dioxide Driven by Temperature Change |journal=[[Science (journal)|Science]] |volume=272 |number=5260 |date=April 19, 1996 |pages=393–396 }}</ref> at 759 times, according to [[Google Scholar]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&as_sdt=0%2C44&q=Ronald+Amundson&btnG= |title=Ronald G. Amundson |publisher=[[Google Scholar]] |accessdate=December 27, 2017}}</ref>

